name: millerf1234/ncurses_Tetris
description: This repository contains a rough implementation of the game 'Tetris' using the terminal library ncurses. I put this together to see if I could write a game in C++, I chose 'Tetris' since I already had a basic understanding of what the end result should look like, allowing me to focus instead on implimentation. I do not own the rights to 'Tetris'. I did this project entirely in Xcode on my Macbook Pro, which defaults the extension on header files to '.hpp', it is my understanding however that most compilers are not picky on the exact file extension of header files, so having this extension shouldn't be a problem.
